      },
      "edited" : false,
      "score" : 4,
      "creation_date" : 1448955772,
      "post_id" : 5380309,
      "comment_id" : 55785439,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "Documentation is next to useless, however, since the <code>final</code> modifier is not enforced on the implementing class. Your interface signature may simply lie."
    }, {
      "owner" : {
        "account_id" : 255665,
        "reputation" : 235280,
        "user_id" : 535871,
        "user_type" : "registered",
        "accept_rate" : 84,
        "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/nhcvo.jpg?s=256",
        "display_name" : "Ted Hopp",
        "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/535871/ted-hopp"
      },
      "edited" : false,
      "score" : 0,
      "creation_date" : 1464125530,
      "post_id" : 5380309,
      "comment_id" : 62353703,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "The Java 8 language spec now says that there are <a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/specs/jls/se8/html/jls-4.html#jls-4.12.3\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">eight kinds of variables</a> (up from seven--they added <i>lambda parameters</i>). Method parameters are still fourth on the list (at least some things in life seem stable. :-))."
    } ],
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 255665,
      "reputation" : 235280,
      "user_id" : 535871,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 84,
