      "comment_id" : 31458232,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "Ok. It&#39;s not really a correct answer to the question, (since I&#39;m not forced to make my implementation of the interface method take final arguments, even if the interface says so), but it&#39;s still helpful, in that it&#39;s a nice explanation of why making method parameters final is a good idea to begin with."
